What does this program print?

```cpp
#include <iostream>

int main() {
    constexpr int base = 5;
    constexpr int squared = base * base;
    constexpr int cubed = squared * base;
    std::cout << cubed << "\n";
    return 0;
}
```

Which of the following will cause a compile error?

```cpp
// A:
const int a = 10;
constexpr int b = a + 5;

// B:
int x = 10;
constexpr int c = x + 5;
```

A student writes this program and expects it to compile. What is wrong?

```cpp
#include <iostream>

int main() {
    int n;
    std::cin >> n;
    constexpr int doubled = n * 2;
    std::cout << doubled << "\n";
    return 0;
}
```

What does this program print?

```cpp
#include <iostream>

int main() {
    constexpr int width = 7;
    constexpr int height = 3;
    constexpr int perimeter = 2 * (width + height);
    std::cout << perimeter << "\n";
    return 0;
}
```
